== Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}. Thinly
slice the @button mushrooms{4%ounce} and @garlic{2%clove}.

== Sausage and Mushrooms ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
the @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce}. Break up the meat into pieces until browned,
about ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the mushrooms, onions, and half the garlic to the pan. Stir and toss,
~{3-4%minutes}, until softened.

Add the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon} to a #medium pot{} along with 1 1/2 cups water and
the @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a simmer, and add the
@Israeli couscous{3/4%cup}. Cook about ~{15%minutes}, uncovered, until the Israeli
couscous is done.

> TIP: If the liquid absorbs before the Israeli couscous is done, add a bit more water.

== Spinach ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil and the remaining garlic in another medium pan over
medium heat. Cook ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the @spinach{5%ounce}. Toss
~{3-4%minutes}, until wilted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Finish ==

Stir the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} into the Israeli couscous. Divide between #bowls{},
top with the Italian sausage mixture and the sautéed spinach, and enjoy!